Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["\<\
2. A Partial Introduction to Localization and Fourier Analysis\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9806122473340683`*^9, 3.980612272489726*^9}, {
  3.980621887390874*^9, 
  3.980621887513867*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6a4e3784-791d-4a23-8155-\
178ac5fb54a3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Consider a particle somewhere in a one-dimensional box of length ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["L", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "08d9ac2e-4b7a-4be1-b0fb-46cdafa9d831"],
 ". We\[CloseCurlyQuote]ll have the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["x", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fb3f8744-9dd2-41e6-81a0-9432da3645e3"],
 " coordinate describing the box run from ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"-", 
    FractionBox["L", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3ba695e7-3c7d-4a0f-8cdf-4560fc3f9232"],
 " to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox["L", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e592f25d-662d-4871-8793-c9925aee953c"],
 ". Later I will set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"L", "=", "4"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c44e354e-6e48-4830-95e4-3b261c42ed86"],
 " for definiteness.\n\nTo illustrate localization, we would like to \
construct a wave function out of sines and cosines that localize the particle \
within the region ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"x", "=", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"-", "L"}], "8"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0057f76d-48d1-4acd-8aba-3d9f2679f31f"],
 " to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"x", "=", 
    FractionBox["L", "8"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "77461ae3-a84e-4c4e-82ee-8c6a9a13d873"],
 ". If the particle is going to be evenly-likely found within this range, \
which is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox["L", "4"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3ee82a08-a12e-4362-ab85-9e3c3bd3c2bd"],
 " long, one way to do that is to have its amplitude be the constant",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SqrtBox[
     FractionBox["4", "L"]],
    FontSize->14], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8684866c-34c2-421e-96a6-6e75e51987af"],
 " within this range, and zero elsewhere.\n\nBecause I have chosen a \
localization that is symmetrical about the origin, it turns out we don\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]t need sines and cosines. We only need the cosines because \
they are symmetric (even) whereas the sines are antisymmetric (odd).\n\nSome \
general considerations based on boundary conditions are that the only cosines \
we have to consider are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox[
     SqrtBox[
      FractionBox["2", "L"]],
     FontSize->14], "cos", " ", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"n", " ", "\[Pi]", " ", "x"}], "L"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"afdbe886-b86f-48a0-ba83-6145f9fb7fe0"],
 " where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "933fff91-8946-4100-abbc-47d1cc73946a"],
 " is any odd integer. The square root, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    SqrtBox[
     FractionBox["2", "L"]],
    FontSize->14], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "67fcc75c-d53a-432c-9d33-f09c1565e0a4"],
 ", out front is put there so that the average of the function-squared is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox["1", "L"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9640ec2b-83d8-4540-8122-59e9dc459d58"],
 ". If that function were used all by itself as a probability amplitude in \
the box of length ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["L", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f596755b-0bcf-4bba-93bc-19ec5f42f381"],
 ", and we then squared it to get a probability function, then the \
probability to find the particle somewhere in the box would be 1.\n\nThere is \
powerful mathematics from the world of Fourier analysis, which you definitely \
are not meant to understand at the moment, but which I can use to compute the \
appropriate combination of cosines. I will now apply the procedure, which \
involves integration, and I am only going to do it for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"n", "=", "1"}], ",", " ", "3", ",", " ", "5", ",", " ", "...", 
    " ", ",", "15"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "16bdbe2c-5476-4994-9d71-4ec59b26cba6"],
 ". If you want to go past ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"n", "=", "15"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "567831ca-f4b5-4c8a-b8f3-bee3ea0337d3"],
 " (it is an infinite series) feel free to go further.\n\nSince we are only \
doing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "147563f6-50e1-4650-b887-acbd6a708617"],
 " odd, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"n", "=", "15"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "18fa7db8-5dad-4672-8542-17bd8e110a03"],
 " is actually just the first 8 cosines in the series."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9774848339897337`*^9, 3.9774848607646503`*^9}, {
   3.977484927744688*^9, 3.9774850172470627`*^9}, {3.977486488535474*^9, 
   3.977487002002028*^9}, {3.977487032886286*^9, 3.977487041522026*^9}, 
   3.977487077838335*^9, {3.977487132003697*^9, 3.9774871324542837`*^9}, {
   3.977487238050396*^9, 3.9774874168568783`*^9}, {3.980609860842248*^9, 
   3.980609872855412*^9}, {3.980610981034216*^9, 3.980610999165991*^9}, {
   3.980612279123908*^9, 3.980612408054124*^9}, {3.980612501992551*^9, 
   3.980612502265012*^9}, {3.9806125393464813`*^9, 3.980612684014167*^9}, {
   3.9806127175420513`*^9, 3.9806128289693317`*^9}, {3.980619784885008*^9, 
   3.980619804550033*^9}, {3.980619847049222*^9, 3.98061985135075*^9}, {
   3.980621217755962*^9, 
   3.9806213272639313`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ff94d879-65bb-4584-9319-\
79981658d393"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"L", "=", "4"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"c", "[", 
    RowBox[{"x_", ",", "n_"}], "]"}], ":=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Sqrt", "[", 
     FractionBox["2", "L"], "]"}], 
    RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"n", "\[VeryThinSpace] ", "Pi", " ", "x"}], "L"], "]"}]}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"tableOfCoefficients", "=", 
  RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Integrate", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Sqrt", "[", 
        FractionBox["4", "L"], "]"}], 
       RowBox[{"c", "[", 
        RowBox[{"x", ",", "n"}], "]"}]}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", 
        FractionBox[
         RowBox[{"-", "L"}], "8"], ",", 
        FractionBox["L", "8"]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"n", ",", "1", ",", "15", ",", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]}], "Input",\

 CellChangeTimes->{{3.977487424238192*^9, 3.9774876121370687`*^9}, {
   3.977487891651101*^9, 3.977487894152358*^9}, {3.977488179638844*^9, 
   3.9774882240589952`*^9}, 3.9774890232690163`*^9, {3.980609791825385*^9, 
   3.980609791879828*^9}, 3.980609836361867*^9, {3.980611055950932*^9, 
   3.980611138811013*^9}, {3.9806128352229137`*^9, 3.9806128652398977`*^9}, {
   3.98062127670931*^9, 3.9806212768104753`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[12]:=",ExpressionUUID->"328a0e2d-96d2-4075-8a94-62e5b11f9c8d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"4", " ", 
     SqrtBox["2"], " ", 
     RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
      FractionBox["\[Pi]", "8"], "]"}]}], "\[Pi]"], ",", 
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"2", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Csc", "[", 
      FractionBox["\[Pi]", "8"], "]"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"3", " ", "\[Pi]"}]], ",", 
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"2", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Csc", "[", 
      FractionBox["\[Pi]", "8"], "]"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"5", " ", "\[Pi]"}]], ",", 
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"4", " ", 
     SqrtBox["2"], " ", 
     RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
      FractionBox["\[Pi]", "8"], "]"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"7", " ", "\[Pi]"}]], ",", 
   RowBox[{"-", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"4", " ", 
      SqrtBox["2"], " ", 
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       FractionBox["\[Pi]", "8"], "]"}]}], 
     RowBox[{"9", " ", "\[Pi]"}]]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"-", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"2", " ", 
      RowBox[{"Csc", "[", 
       FractionBox["\[Pi]", "8"], "]"}]}], 
     RowBox[{"11", " ", "\[Pi]"}]]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"-", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"2", " ", 
      RowBox[{"Csc", "[", 
       FractionBox["\[Pi]", "8"], "]"}]}], 
     RowBox[{"13", " ", "\[Pi]"}]]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"-", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"4", " ", 
      SqrtBox["2"], " ", 
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       FractionBox["\[Pi]", "8"], "]"}]}], 
     RowBox[{"15", " ", "\[Pi]"}]]}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.980609838103446*^9, 3.9806111399770412`*^9, {3.980612838271072*^9, 
   3.980612865636909*^9}, 3.980620103478855*^9, {3.980620404095036*^9, 
   3.980620430141183*^9}, 3.980620471110373*^9, {3.980620573219695*^9, 
   3.9806205880798397`*^9}, 3.9806212804956713`*^9, 3.980621336765547*^9, 
   3.980621822969095*^9, 3.980818902716457*^9, 3.980818999582078*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[14]=",ExpressionUUID->"31c5b95d-cfdb-48c1-878f-70b2ea69296b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
Perhaps it is nice, and maybe even more convenient to see what these \
coefficients are numerically:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.98062013026538*^9, 3.980620145281402*^9}, {
  3.9806206720185757`*^9, 
